HOWL PHYS-25: BETA NORMALIZATION DIAGNOSTIC
======================================================================

THE THREE CONVENTIONS
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  A (Standard Weyl):  (2/5, 2/3, 2/3) per Weyl fermion
  B (Standard Dirac): (4/5, 4/3, 4/3) per Dirac fermion
  C (Library Dynkin):  (2/5, 2/3, 1/3) per VL pair

  A and B differ by factor 2 uniformly (Weyl vs Dirac).
  C matches A for b_1 and b_2 but has HALF A for b_3.

