  Component                          b_1          b_2          b_3
  ------------------------  ------------ ------------ ------------
  Gauge                                0        -22/3          -11
  Higgs                             1/10          1/6            0
  Fermion (Conv A)                     4            4            4
  Fermion (Conv C)                     4            4            2
  ------------------------  ------------ ------------ ------------
  SM total (Conv A)                41/10        -19/6           -7
  SM total (Conv C)                41/10        -19/6           -9
  Library (DATA-4 N1-N3)           41/10        -19/6           -7

  Convention A reproduces SM betas: True
  Convention C reproduces SM betas: False

  Convention C gives b_3 = -9, library has -7.
  The fermion contribution is 2 (Conv C) vs 4 (Conv A).
  Convention C is WRONG for SM b_3 by a factor of 2.

VL (3,2,1/6) ONE-LOOP SHIFTS
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Convention                        Db_1         Db_2         Db_3
  ------------------------  ------------ ------------ ------------
  A: Weyl (one Weyl)                1/15            1          2/3
  B: Dirac (one Dirac)              2/15            2          4/3
  C: Library formula                1/15            1          1/3
  Library actual (N4-N6)            1/15            1          1/3

  Ratios library_actual / convention:
    vs Weyl      1, 1, 1/2
    vs Dirac     1/2, 1/2, 1/4

  Library formula matches library actual: True
  Library actual matches Weyl: False
    Component 3: library = 1/3, Weyl = 2/3

THE DIVERGENCE: SU(3) COEFFICIENT
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Standard Weyl formula for b_3:
    Db_3 = (2/3) * T(R_3) * dim(R_2)

  Library Dynkin formula for b_3:
    Db_3 = (1/3) * dim(R_2) * S_2(R_3)

  T(R_3) = S_2(R_3) in all cases, so the ONLY
  difference is the coefficient: 2/3 vs 1/3.

  For SM fermions (Convention A, Weyl):
    b_3 fermion = 3 * sum_gen = 3 * 4/3 = 4
    b_3_SM = -11 + 0 + 4 = -7  CORRECT

  For SM fermions (Convention C, library):
    b_3 fermion = 3 * sum_gen = 3 * 2/3 = 2
    b_3_SM = -11 + 0 + 2 = -9  WRONG (should be -7)

  The library's b_3 Dynkin coefficient 1/3 is HALF the
  standard Weyl coefficient 2/3. It does not reproduce
  b_3_SM = -7 when applied to SM fermion fields.

